        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>trawlers [300232749], net fishing vessels [300232744], fishing vessels by function [300254597], fishing vessels [300232733], hunting and commercial fishing vessels [300232732], watercraft by function [300232728], watercraft by specific type [300219289], watercraft [300042940], vehicles (transportation) [300219258], Transportation Vehicles (hierarchy name) [300042929], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small otter trawlers of various types and sizes, which engage in shore fishing along the Atlantic Coast of the United States, usually within 50 miles of the coastline; introduced in the mid-20th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para los palangreros de nutrias pequeños de varios tipos y mediades, los cuales se utilizado en la pesca costera a lo largo de la costa atlántica de Estados Unidos, generalmente dentro de las 50 millas de la línea de costa. Fueron introducidos a mediados del siglo XX.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor kleine otter trawlers van verschilldende soort en grootte die worden gebruikt bij het vissen langs de Atlantische kust van de Verenigde Staten en meestal niet verder gaan dan 80 km uit de kust; zijn halverwege de 20e eeuw geïntroduceerd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>於二十世紀中期引所進之各種型式和尺寸的小型網板拖網船，用於美國大西洋海岸沿線的沿岸漁業，普遍作業於離海岸線50英里以內的海域。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleiner Scherbretttrawler unterschiedlicher Art und Größe, der in der Küstenfischerei entlang der Atlantikküste der Vereinigten Staaten eingesetzt wird, gewöhnlich innerhalb von 80 km vor der Küstenlinie; Mitte des 20. Jahrhunderts eingeführt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
